---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "1 May 2026";
---

<Layout title="Cookie Policy — Purrtraits">
  <section class="legal page">
    <div class="container legal__inner">
      <header class="legal__header">
        <p class="legal__eyebrow">LEGAL</p>
        <h1 class="legal__title display">Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="muted legal__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </header>

      <article class="legal__body">
        <p>
          This Cookie Policy explains how Purrtraits uses cookies and
          similar storage technologies on
          <a href="https://purrtraits.shop">purrtraits.shop</a>
          (the "Site"). It should be read alongside our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, which describes how we
          handle personal data more generally.
        </p>

        <h2 class="legal__h2">1. What are cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you
          visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work,
          remember preferences, and provide information to site
          owners. We also use related technologies such as
          <code>localStorage</code> and <code>sessionStorage</code> in
          your browser; for simplicity we refer to all of these as
          "cookies" in this policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="legal__h2">2. Cookies we use</h2>

        <h3 class="legal__h3">a) Strictly necessary cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These are required for the Site to function and cannot be
          switched off. They are usually only set in response to
          actions you take, such as signing in, filling in forms, or
          adding items to your cart. We rely on legitimate interests
          for these — your consent is not required.
        </p>
        <ul class="legal__list">
          <li>
            <strong>Session ID</strong> — a random identifier that
            links your browser to your cart, quiz answers, and
            generated portraits while you use the Site.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Authentication tokens</strong> — keep you signed
            in across pages once you create an account.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cart state</strong> — remembers what you have
            added to your basket so it survives a refresh.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cookie-consent preferences</strong> — remembers
            your choices about non-essential cookies so we don't ask
            again every visit.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="legal__h3">b) Analytics &amp; advertising cookies</h3>
        <p>
          With your consent, we set cookies to understand how the Site
          is used and to show you advertising. These are set by us and
          by Google AdSense.
        </p>
        <ul class="legal__list">
          <li>
            <strong>Google AdSense</strong> — Google sets cookies
            (including, where applicable, the <code>NID</code>,
            <code>IDE</code>, and <code>__gads</code> /
            <code>__gpi</code> cookies) to serve ads, measure ad
            performance, prevent the same ad being shown repeatedly,
            and — where you opt in to personalised advertising — to
            tailor ads to your interests. For details see
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policies.google.com/technologies/ads</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Product analytics</strong> — basic event logging
            (pages visited, buttons clicked, performance metrics) so
            we can fix issues and improve the product. We do not use
            this data to identify individuals beyond your account.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="legal__h2">3. Managing your cookie choices</h2>
        <p>You can control non-essential cookies in several ways:</p>
        <ul class="legal__list">
          <li>
            <strong>Our cookie banner.</strong> When you first visit
            the Site we ask whether you consent to advertising and
            analytics cookies. You can change your choice at any time
            by clearing your cookies for this Site, which will trigger
            the banner again on your next visit.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Browser settings.</strong> Most browsers let you
            view, block, or delete cookies. Doing so may break parts
            of the Site (for example sign-in or your cart). See the
            help pages for
            <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chrome</a>,
            <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/kb/cookies-information-websites-store-on-your-computer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Firefox</a>,
            <a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Safari</a>,
            or
            <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/microsoft-edge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Edge</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Ads Settings.</strong> You can opt out of
            personalised advertising from Google specifically at
            <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">adssettings.google.com</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Industry opt-outs.</strong> You can opt out of
            many advertising-network cookies via
            <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Your Online Choices</a>
            (for UK and EU users).
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="legal__h2">4. Do Not Track</h2>
        <p>
          Some browsers send a "Do Not Track" signal. There is no
          common industry standard for how to respond to it, so the
          Site does not currently change behaviour based on the
          signal. We do honour the cookie-consent choice you make on
          our banner.
        </p>

        <h2 class="legal__h2">5. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time —
          for example if we add new tools or change advertising
          partners. When we make material changes we will update the
          "Last updated" date above.
        </p>

        <h2 class="legal__h2">6. Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about how we use cookies, email
          <a href="mailto:privacy@purrtraits.shop">privacy@purrtraits.shop</a>.
          For more about how we handle personal data, please read our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal__inner { max-width: 760px; }
  .legal__header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 36px; }
  .legal__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--c-pink);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .legal__title { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .legal__updated { font-size: 14px; }

  .legal__body {
    background: var(--c-white);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--c-stroke-light);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    padding: 28px 22px;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--c-dark);
  }
  .legal__body p { margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .legal__body a { color: var(--c-pink); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .legal__body a:hover { color: #c98399; }
  .legal__body code {
    background: var(--c-fill);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1px 6px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .legal__body ul.legal__list {
    margin: 6px 0 18px 22px;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .legal__body ul.legal__list li { margin-bottom: 8px; }

  .legal__h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 26px;
    color: var(--c-dark);
    margin: 28px 0 10px;
    padding-bottom: 6px;
    border-bottom: 1.5px solid var(--c-pink-light);
  }
  .legal__h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--c-dark);
    margin: 18px 0 6px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .legal__body { padding: 44px 48px; font-size: 16px; }
    .legal__h2 { font-size: 30px; }
    .legal__h3 { font-size: 22px; }
  }
</style>
